articles.title: Turkey coup anniversary: Emotional Erdogan hails 'defenders of nation'
articles.description: Turkey's president thanks those who "defended the nation" against the coup attempt a year ago.

articles.author: BBC News
articles.title: Eight dead in wall collapse at Senegal's Demba Diop
articles.description: A wall collapsed during clashes following a League Cup final at Dakar's Demba Diop stadium.

articles.author: BBC News
articles.title: Chile turns chilly as Santiago hit by rare heavy snowfall
articles.description: A cold snap in Santiago leads to blackouts, leaving about 250,000 residents without power.

articles.author: BBC News
articles.title: Ancient underwater forest found in US
articles.description: Scientists have dated the trees to a previous ice age 60,000 years ago, when sea levels were far lower.

articles.title: Acid attack punishments assessed in government review

articles.title: US brides-to-be left dressless as Alfred Angelo folds
articles.description: US brides-to-be in the limbo as dressmaker folds.

articles.author: BBC News
articles.title: Brazil protesters pelt politician with eggs at her wedding
articles.description: Maria Victoria Barros is forced to leave church in an armoured vehicle and protected by riot police.

articles.author: BBC Sport
articles.title: Wimbledon 2017: Roger Federer going for eighth title against Marin Cilic in final
articles.description: Roger Federer will attempt to become the first man to win eight Wimbledon titles when he takes on Marin Cilic in Sunday's final.

articles.author: BBC News
articles.title: G20 Hamburg: Tag potential rioters, German interior minister says
articles.description: The government is seeking to prevent a repeat of rioting which marred the G20 summit in Hamburg.

articles.title: Maryam Mirzakhani, first woman to win maths' Fields Medal, dies
